review 1:
Food was delicious but I don’t like that they have two pricing system for locals and tourists. Our driver took us here saying it’s a cheap local place for under R50K. However, we ended up paying R75k per dish. I know it’s not expensive but just don’t like the two pricing system or they should be up front about it.

We ate at other road side warugs and sate stalls etc and were charged the same price as locals.

Maybe we had our dish deconstructed, whereas the locals were all on the same plate.
